report.measDesc: This parcel layer contains discrete, non-overlapping polygons for each property. Adjacent polygons with common ownership and a single tax record have been retained in the "OthLeg" layer that accompanies this TaxPar layer, and dissolved into single parcels in this TaxPar layer. Some non-adjacent parcels may be represented by multi-part polygons where they share common ownership and a single tax record. Public right of ways exist as polygons, not null space. Linework associated with private ROWs are retained in the "OthLeg" layer. Water polygons also representing parcel boundaries have been retained in this TaxPar layer. Additional water features that are not considered parcel boundaries may have been placed in the "Misc" layer that accompanies this TaxPar layer. Easements and other similar non-fee taxable boundaries exist in the 'OthLeg" layer, not the TaxPar layer.

prcStep.stepDesc: Source geodatabase converted to MassGIS level 3 standard. During the conversion process the data is manipulated with ESRI tools to project, dissolve, copy, calculate, and generally manipulate the ESRI version of the source data to meet Mass GIS Level III standards. Updated through FY20 in September 2019

overview.dsoverv: M072TaxPar represents a version of digital municipal parcels for the community of DARTMOUTH that is considered level 3 compliant per the specifications outlined in the MassGIS Standard for Digital Parcel Files. Its features can be linked in a GIS or database environment to a set of standardized assessing attributes in the table M072Assess by using the unique identifying values in the LOC_ID field. This data is also intended to be used in conjunction with associated (and optional) features in the ancillary data layers M072OthLeg and M072Misc. As one of the data sets identified by Massachusetts Strategic Plan for Spatial Data Infrastructure (http:/ /www.mass.gov/mgis/stratplan.html), this data enters the public domain as a valuable resource for mapping, planning, and analysis at all levels of government as well as the private sector.
